## Why This Is Asked
Assesses ability to design scalable feature flags with per-user rollout, regional controls, and safe hot flips.

## Key Concepts
- Global distribution and eventual consistency
- Data modeling for flags and segments
- Cache invalidation and TTL
- Rollout semantics and hot-flip safety

## Code Example
```javascript
function evaluateFeature(user, flag, context){
  const bucket = hash(user.id + flag.name) % 100;
  const inSegment = (flag.segments && flag.segments.length) ? flag.segments.includes(user.segment) : true;
  const regionOK = flag.regionOverride ? user.region === flag.regionOverride : true;
  return (bucket < flag.rolloutPct) && inSegment && regionOK;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate rollout accuracy under traffic spikes?
- How would you rollback a faulty flag without service interruption?

