## Why This Is Asked

Assess real-world troubleshooting, instrumentation, and change-management skills under production-like pressure. It probes how a candidate reasons about observability, bottlenecks, and safe rollbacks in a live system.

## Key Concepts

- Observability: p95/p99 latency, error rate, queue depth, throughput
- Backpressure and rate limiting: bounded queues, controlled retries
- Idempotency and safety: ensure duplicates don’t break state
- Canary and rollback strategies

## Code Example

```javascript
// Simple rate limiter example (token bucket)
function createRateLimiter(tokensPerWindow, windowMs) {
  let tokens = tokensPerWindow; let t0 = Date.now();
  return function allow() {
    const now = Date.now();
    const elapsed = now - t0;
    if (elapsed > windowMs) { t0 = now; tokens = tokensPerWindow; }
    if (tokens > 0) { tokens--; return true; }
    return false;
  };
}
```

