- Real-time drift detection in Flink processing pipeline
- Automated quarantine and alerting mechanisms
- Circuit breaker patterns for data quality protection

## Code Example
```java
// Flink schema validation with drift detection
public class SchemaValidator extends ProcessFunction<GenericRecord, GenericRecord> {
    private final SchemaRegistryClient registry;

    @Override
    public void processElement(GenericRecord record, Context ctx) {
        try {
            Schema schema = registry.getLatestSchema(tenantTopic);
            if (!isValidAgainstSchema(record, schema)) {
                ctx.output(quarantineTag, record);
                alertDashboard("SCHEMA_DRIFT", tenantTopic);
            } else {
                ctx.output(validTag, record);
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            ctx.output(errorTag, record);
        }
    }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
