## Why This Is Asked

Evaluates practical fintech security decisions: key management, rotating keys, PKCE, mTLS, replay protection, and observability trade-offs.

## Key Concepts

- OAuth2-like flows with PKCE
- JWT rotation and key management (HSM backing)
- mTLS and token binding
- Replay protection (nonce, jti)
- Observability, rate limits, and revocation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Token verification sketch
function verifyToken(token, keystore) {
  const { header } = parseJwt(token);
  const key = keystore.getKey(header.kid);
  const payload = verifyJwt(token, key);
  if (!payload) return false;
  if (payload.exp * 1000 < Date.now()) return false;
  return payload.aud.includes("api");
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test key rotation without downtime?
- How would you detect token abuse and adapt rate limits?
